    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - CAB: 5000, 9100, 9200, 9300, 9400 - REMOVE AND INSTALL -
        WINDSHIELD WASHERS WITH AIR WIPERS
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="2">
        <title>WINDSHIELD WASHERS WITH AIR WIPERS</title>
        <para>The windshield washers have an integral reservoir and electric pump motor located inside the engine
            compartment (
            <hotlnk xrefid="f1600596">Figure 96</hotlnk>) on the right side cab bulkhead. The windshield washer is
            activated by a push button switch (
            <hotlnk document="s16005v_50.xml" xrefid="f1600591">Item 6, Figure 91</hotlnk>) on the wiper/washer control
            panel (
            <hotlnk document="s16005v_50.xml" xrefid="f1600591">Item 7, Figure 91</hotlnk>) on the header panel. The
            washer hoses are mounted in the header panel before September 1994.
        </para>
        <para>The washer hoses are routed from the reservoir-mounted pump motor (
            <hotlnk xrefid="f1600596">Item 5, Figure 96</hotlnk>), through the bulkhead to a T-fitting (
            <hotlnk xrefid="f1600597">Item 1, Figure 97</hotlnk>) inside the header panel behind the passenger side
            (right) wiper motor cover panel (
            <hotlnk document="s16005v_51.xml" xrefid="f1600594">Item 1, Figure 94</hotlnk>). From the T-fitting, the
            hoses go to the washer fitting (
            <hotlnk document="s16005v_49.xml" xrefid="f1600589">Item 2, Figure 89</hotlnk>) on the cab roof above the
            wipers, and from there to the individual nozzles on the wiper arms.
        </para>
